# Next.js Architecture

## Server Components First

Default to Server Components. Only add `"use client"` when the component genuinely needs browser APIs (`useState`, `useEffect`, `onClick`, animations).

```tsx
// BAD — "use client" just to render static content
"use client";
export default function ProductSpec({ data }) { ... }

// GOOD — static content stays on the server
export default function ProductSpec({ data }) { ... }
```

## Metadata in Server Components

Export `metadata` and render JSON-LD `<script>` tags in `page.tsx` (server component), never inside a `"use client"` component.

## Dynamic Imports for Heavy Components

Wrap large client components with `dynamic()` to keep the initial bundle small:

```tsx
const QuoteModal = dynamic(() => import("@/components/QuoteModal"), {
  ssr: false,
});
```

## Static Export

This site uses `output: "export"`. No dynamic routes, no `generateStaticParams`, no server-side APIs. All pages are statically generated at build time.

## Component Responsibility

Each component does one thing. A `ProductCard` displays a product. A `QuoteModal` handles the quote form. Do not combine unrelated concerns.

## Data Separation

Product specs, feature lists, and client testimonials live in data objects — not scattered through JSX markup.
